cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the task of semantic alignment of images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a convolutional neural network architecture that is trainable in an end-to-end manner, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a differentiable soft inlier scoring module, which is inspired by the RANSAC inlier scoring procedure, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions that it achieves state-of-the-art performance on multiple standard benchmarks for semantic alignment, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
